            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "Sw9I9",
              "name": "H",
              "fill": "$cream",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": 1400,
              "content": "Capital that goes first, so other capital can follow.",
              "lineHeight": 1.1,
              "fontFamily": "$display",
              "fontSize": 58,
              "fontWeight": "600"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "xDhMl",
          "name": "Body",
          "fill": "$onDark",
          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
          "width": 1500,
          "content": "Grants alone build dependence. Commercial lenders will not fund a community-owned plant before the economics are proven. Catalytic capital sits in between. It is patient, it tolerates risk, and it is structured to be recovered or to convert into community ownership. It de-risks the press so government demand and concessional debt can follow.",
          "lineHeight": 1.5,
          "fontFamily": "$body",
          "fontSize": 25,
          "fontWeight": "normal"
        },
